Lizeka Tandwa, News24Pretoria - At least 400 people barricaded roads during a protest in Irene, south of Pretoria, on Thursday morning. - Send us your eyewitness accounts and photos. Police spokesperson Brigadier Mathapelo Peters said Gauteng public order police officials are on high alert, and are monitoring the R21 highway.She said police managed to disperse the crowd. They are unaware of what sparked the protest."Police together with South African National Road Agency managed to clear the road for traffic flow. We are currently monitoring the area for any activity," she said.#sapsGP #R21 southbound has been cleared following #ProtestAction. R21 northbound is still being cleared. NP&mdash; SA Police Service (@SAPoliceService) May 4, 2017#sapsGP #R21 southbound has been cleared following #ProtestAction. R21 northbound is still being cleared. NP97347: Road closed R21 Northbound &amp; Southbound before &amp; after Nellmapius Dr due to protest action. pic.twitter.com/92NejIAw8d&mdash; ITRAFFIC (GP) (@itrafficgp) May 4, 201797347: Road closed R21 Northbound &amp; Southbound before &amp; after Nellmapius Dr due to protest action. pic.twitter.com/92NejIAw8d24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.